=== Contraindications — Do Not Proceed with Descent Work If:

#safety[
  The following conditions contraindicate the deep descent practices introduced in Year One Month 6. These are not administrative suggestions — proceeding with descent work while a contraindication applies creates risks the Academy cannot mitigate and the student cannot reliably manage without professional support.
]

- Current experience of acute psychosis, mania, or severe dissociation
- Significant traumatic event within the past six months without active professional processing
- Diagnosed dissociative disorder (DID or OSDD) without a currently active treating therapist
- Untreated panic disorder that has triggered during meditation or closed-eye visualisation
- Any acute mental health crisis
- Active suicidal ideation

#risk-item(
  "psychological destabilisation arising from descent practices",
