)

=== Mandatory Cessation Thresholds

The following conditions require a Guide to immediately cease all inner work instruction and direct the student to external crisis resources. These are administrative thresholds, not clinical judgments.

A Guide must cease inner work instruction when a student reports or demonstrates:

+ Active suicidal ideation — any expression of intent or plan to end their life
+ Acute psychotic symptoms — loss of contact with reality outside the context of the waking dream practice
+ Inability to distinguish waking dream imagery from physical reality beyond the session itself
+ Self-harm behaviour within the reporting period
+ Prolonged dissociation — inability to return to ordinary awareness more than 24 hours after a session
+ Expressed intent to harm another person

Upon reaching any threshold, the Guide stops instruction, provides crisis resources, notifies the Headmaster, and does not attempt counselling. See Crisis-Response SOP.

=== What Guides Are and Are Not

Guides are Educational Facilitators — practitioners who have completed the curriculum and are qualified to support engagement with its content. They are not licensed mental health professionals. They do not assess psychological health, provide therapy, or conduct crisis intervention. See the Guide Code of Conduct & Educational Facilitator Agreement.

=== Grounding After a Difficult Session

If a practice produces distress or difficulty returning to ordinary awareness:

+ Stop the practice immediately
+ Ground physically: press feet on the floor, feel the chair beneath you, name three objects aloud
+ Breathe: three slow deliberate breaths with full exhale
+ Do something ordinary: drink water, wash hands, go outside briefly
+ Write briefly in the journal: a factual account of what occurred
+ Do not attempt another session the same day
+ Contact your Guide before the next scheduled session

=== Referral Pathway

The Academy does not provide referrals or endorse specific practitioners. Students are solely responsible for identifying, vetting, and engaging their own mental health professionals. Applicable crisis resources by jurisdiction are listed in the Crisis-Response SOP.

If you are in crisis, contact your local emergency mental health service or crisis line immediately:
- *US:* 988 Suicide & Crisis Lifeline (call or text 988)
- *Oregon specifically:* Lines for Life 1-800-273-8255
- *International:* findahelpline.com

=== Oregon Law Note

Oregon Revised Statutes Chapter 675 governs the practice of psychology, clinical social work, marriage and family therapy, and professional counselling. The Academy does not engage in any practice regulated under ORS Chapter 675. No Guide or Headmaster represents themselves as providing any ORS 675-regulated service.

